<F P=100> Sub-Saharan Africa </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Suspends Diplomatic Ties With Burkina Faso </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0502112294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1053 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0502112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 5 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese 
Government has lodged a strong protest with the Government of 
Burkina Faso and declared the suspension of China's diplomatic 
relations with Burkina Faso. 
  According to reports from Ouagadougou, Li Yongqian, Chinese 
ambassador to Burkina Faso, made serious representations with 
the Government of Burkina Faso yesterday. He solemnly stated 
that as the Government of Burkina Faso had "restored" the 
so-called "diplomatic relations" with the Taiwan authorities, 
the Chinese Government lodged a strong protest with the 
Government of Burkina Faso and declared the suspension of 
China's diplomatic ties with Burkina Faso. 
  Li pointed out that by doing so, the Burkina Faso Government 
had gone back on its solemn commitment contained in the 
communique of September 15, 1973 on the establishment of 
diplomatic relations between China and Burkina Faso that it 
recognized the Government of the People's Republic of China as 
the sole legal government representing the entire Chinese 
people, seriously undermining the existing friendly relations 
and cooperation between the two countries and the friendship 
between the two peoples. 
  He announced that the Government of the People's Republic of 
China decided, therefore, to suspend its diplomatic relations 
with Burkina Faso as of that day. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-26389 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi025_w_94001" </HT>


