<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Motors To Enter Joint Venture To Produce Engines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0702140594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1344 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0702140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 7 (XINHUA) -- The General Motors 
Corporation (GM) and its two Chinese counterparts plan to set up 
a joint venture producing a new kind of motor engine controller. 
  The venture will produce 300,000 such controllers a year and 
the output could hit 600,000 when the market demand increases. 
  The new engine controlling system cuts fuel consumption by 5 
to 10 percent while decreasing waste gas by 60 to 90 percent, 
compared with the old system. 
  China has listed the system as a key national project in the 
Eighth Five-Year Plan period and the Ninth Five-Year Plan. 
  The two Chinese corporations are the Beijing Wanyuan 
Industrial Corporation and the Beijing Economic Investment and 
Development Corporation. 
  The new venture, Beijing Wanyuan-General Motor 
Electronic-Control Co. Ltd., will start with a 30 million U.S. 
dollar investment, to be followed by another 120 million U.S. 
dollars. 
  The new venture will use the technology of the American 
vehicle manufacturing giant. 

</TEXT>

