<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Xinjiang's Acting Chairman Addresses Foreign Trade Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0502173194 Urumqi Xinjiang Television Network in Mandarin 
1330 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0502173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Urumqi Xinjiang Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video from the "Xinjiang News" </F>
program] 
  [Text] Our region's total export and import volume 
amounted to $912 million in 1993, 36.42 times more than in the 
prereform years. An extensive pattern of opening up to the 
outside world in economic relations and trade has initially 
taken shape. 
  In 1993, our region continued to implement the strategic 
principles of opening up to the outside world in all directions, 
paying special attention to areas in the west, importing from 
abroad and cooperating with units in the interior, and 
establishing economic ties with regions in the east and 
distributing products to those in the west, thereby achieving 
fairly satisfactory results in foreign economic relations and 
trade. Total export and import volume amounted to $912 million, 
an increase of 30 percent over 1992. Of this, local border 
trade continued to grow rapidly; total local border trade volume 
reached $570 million in 1993, an increase of 80 percent over 
1992 or 68.3 percent of the region's total foreign trade volume. 
  Abulaidi Amudurexiti, deputy secretary of the autonomous 
regional party committee and acting chairman of the autonomous 
regional government, spoke at an autonomous regional work 
conference on foreign economic relations and trade that was held 
yesterday. He said: The year 1994 is one in which the 
autonomous region will develop its economy rapidly on the basis 
of high efficiency, and will advance reform of the foreign trade 
system. We should seize the current favorable situation in 
international markets, do a good job of earning foreign exchange 
from exports, and steadily develop local border trade while 
incessantly improving economic returns. We should improve the 
investment environment, and expand the scale of utilizing 
foreign capital and economic and technological cooperation. 
  Regional leaders Wang Lequan, Keyum Bawudun, Aisihaiti 
Kelimubai, and Li Donghui attended yesterday's conference. 

</TEXT>

