<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sichuan Province Completes More Infrastructure Projects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0802104494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0619 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0802104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chengdu, February 8 (XINHUA) -- More key 
infrastructure projects have been completed or gone into 
operation in southwest China's Sichuan Province, greatly 
boosting the local economic prosperity. 
  The projects are mainly in the transportation, 
telecommunications, energy, water conservancy and raw material 
production sectors, according to officials of the provincial 
office for the construction of key projects. 
  The projects include an expressway between Chengdu and 
Chongqing, the second-phase construction of a digital 
telecommunications network, the Tongjiezi Hydropower Station, 
the second-phase construction of the Panzhihua Iron and Steel 
Company, the Longchang-Luzhou railway line, a chemical 
fertilizer plant, a chemical plant and a cement plant. 
  The Sichuan section of an optical fiber telecommunications 
cable line between Xian, capital of Shaanxi Province in 
northwest China, and Chengdu, capital of Sichuan, have been 
completed. 
  For a long time the backward infrastructure had hampered 
this 
inland province's economic development. 
  Last year Sichuan invested nearly nine billion yuan (over 
one 
billion U.S. dollars) in the construction of 60 construction 
projects -- both figures setting records for the province. 
  The responsibility system has been used for the construction 
of some projects, as a reform measure, to ensure quality and 
progress of construction, production, management and repayment 
of loans. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

