<H3> <TI>   Leaders Attend Spring Festival Celebrations </TI></H3>
<H4>   Li Ruihuan Attends Beijing's Party </H4>
<F P=102> OW0702132494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1311 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0702132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 7 (XINHUA) -- People and 
officials of all nationalities of China attended a get-together 
in Beijing to celebrate the spring festival. 
  Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the 
Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), and Buhe, 
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's 
Congress, attended the get-together. 
  Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee 
and head of the United Front Work Department of the Chinese 
Communist Party Central Committee, said in a speech at the 
get-together that China is a united country with multiple 
nationalities. The current situation on nationalities work is 
good, which shows that the nationality policy of the party is 
correct. 
  Wang said that over the past decades, more and more 
officials 
from minority nationalities had been encouraged and fostered and 
they had played an important role in safeguarding the 
unification of the motherland and enhancing the unity of 
nationalities. 
  He said the establishment of the socialist market economic 
structure will bring opportunities for the economic development 
in the regions of China's minority nationalities. 
  He called for seizing the opportunity so as to accelerate 
development and promote prosperity in these regions. 
  His speech was followed by an excellent performance of songs 
and dances. 

</TEXT>

