<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders Visit Former Party, State Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0802140394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1357 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0802140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 8 (XINHUA) -- Some Chinese leaders 
have visited former party and state leaders in Beijing and 
Shanghai, extending Spring Festival greetings to them. 
  The leaders, from the Central Committee of the Communist 
Party of China (CPC), the Standing Committee of the National 
People's Congress (NPC), the State Council and the national 
committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference (CPPCC), were entrusted to make the visits by the 
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China. 
  Among them were Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the NPC 
Standing 
Committee, Qian Qichen, vice-premier, Wen Jiabao, alternate 
member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, and 
Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the CPPCC national committee. 

</TEXT>

