<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on Leaders' Activities 28 Jan-3 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0502080094 </F>
<F P=103> OW0502080094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] PRC media carried the following reports 
on PRC leadership activities from 28 January to 3 February 1994. 
The source is noted in parentheses after each report. 
<H3>  Li Peng Donates to Jiangxi School </H3>
Premier Li Peng recently sent 500 yuan to the Xiwang (Hope) 
Primary School in Ninggang County, Jiangxi Province. It was 
built from donations for the Hope Project by personnel from CPC 
Central Committee organs and state organs. When the school was 
inaugurated on 19 October 1993, Premier Li Peng inscribed its 
name in his own handwriting. (Beijing Central Television 
Program One Network in Mandarin 1100 GMT 28 Jan 94) 
<H3>  Li Ruihuan Visits Scientist </H3>
Li Ruihuan, member of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau 
Standing Committee and chairman of the CPPCC national committee, 
called on eminent scientist Qian Xuesen at his home in Beijing 
on 3 February. Upon entering his house, Li Ruihuan firmly 
grasped Qian Xuesen's hands and said: "I have been asked by the 
principal leading comrades of the CPC Central Committee and by 
some veteran comrades of the CPPCC national committee to wish 
you a happy Chinese New Year and to convey their season's 
greetings to you and your wife!" Speaking highly of Qian 
Xuesen's outstanding contributions to China's natural science 
and particularly to the space industry, Li Ruihuan said: "China 
successfully tested an atomic bomb and a hydrogen bomb and 
launched a satellite shortly after its liberation. They laid a 
solid foundation for its scientific research as well as the 
development of its space industry. The great influence they 
produced is still felt today. China's atomic bomb, hydrogen 
bomb, and satellite are associated with the name of Qian Xuesen. 
You have conducted intensive research in not only natural 
science, but also social sciences." Li Ruihuan said: "Social 
development is inseparable from the advance of natural science 
and, meanwhile, requires the leadership to make decisions 
scientifically. At present, China keeps improving the 
scientific and democratic decision-making by its leadership. It 
is hoped that you will make more suggestions in this 
connection." (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0834 
GMT 3 Feb 94) 
<H3>  Liu Huaqing Inscribes New Barracks </H3>
Fishermen of Leyuan Village in Changdao County, Shandong 
Province, pooled over 800,000 yuan's worth of funds to erect a 
five-story building as barracks for a special task company 
stationed in the area. Construction of the building was 
recently completed and villagers helped servicemen move into 
their new quarters. Central Military Commission Vice Chairman 
Liu Huaqing was deeply touched by the local fishermen's 
enthusiastic support for the army. He took pleasure in 
inscribing the new building's name. His inscription reads: 
"Yong Jun Lou [Support-the-Army Building]." (Beijing XINHUA 
Domestic Service in Chinese 0535 GMT 2 Feb 94) 
<H3>  Liu Huaqing Meets `Hero' </H3>
On 3 February, Central Military Commission [CMC] Vice Chairmen 
Liu Huaqing and Zhang Zhen met with Xu Honggang, 22, squad 
leader of a signal company of the Jinan Military Region. He was 
stabbed 14 times when fighting off four armed robbers to rescue 
a woman passenger on a bus in August 1993. Liu Huaqing said 
during the meeting: "Your deed of valor is very touching. You 
are a good son of the people and a hero of the People's 
Liberation Army. You protected the people and they saved you. 
It fully shows that, when the army and people are united as 
one, justice will vanquish evil. We are the people's own army. 
We must always firmly bear in mind our purpose of serving the 
people wholeheartedly. We must give top priority to the 
interests of the people and the party under all circumstances 
and at all times and must stand ready to sacrifice everything we 
have for the protection of the partys' and people's interests 
when necessary. We must have a high degree of such 
consciousness and cherish such noble value." Liu Huaqing urged 
all the army's commanders and fighters to learn from Xu Honggang 
and to make greater contributions to the building of socialist 
spiritual civilization. Zhang Zhen said: "We must firmly bear 
in mind the duty of a revolutionary soldier; we must stand all 
tests; we must always maintain the Red Army's true qualities and 
carry forward the fine traditions of the people's army; we must 
set an example of implementing the party's basic line and be a 
strong pillar of people's democratic dictatorship; we must 
always meet political qualification." During the meeting, CMC 
members Chi Haotian, Zhang Wannian, and Yu Yongbo "encouraged Xu 
Honggang to apply himself to the study of political and military 
affairs and to keep improving himself, and called on all the 
army units to promote the drive to learn from Xu Honggang to a 
new climax." (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1128 
GMT 3 Feb 94) 
<H5>  Liu Huaqing, Zhang Zhen Visit Army Unit </H5>
  Accompanied by Gu Shanqing, political commissar of the 
Beijing Military Region [BMR], and He Daoquan [0149 6670 3123], 
deputy commander of the BMR and commander of the Beijing 
Garrison, Liu Huaqing and Zhang Zhen, vice chairmen of the 
Central Military Commission [CMC], went to the barracks of a 
hero BMR company on 31 January to wish its officers and men a 
happy Chinese New Year on behalf of the CMC. The company have 
carried on the Red Army's glorious traditions. Liu Huaqing and 
Zhang Zhen inspected the company's quarters and mess halls, 
enquired about servicemen's food and living conditions, and 
required company leaders to show concern for new recruits. They 
prohibited company leaders from beating or abusing new recruits. 
During inspection, Liu Huaqing said: "It is hoped that, in the 
new year, comrades will make continued efforts, establish higher 
standards, carry forward the traditions of Red Army veterans in 
a better way, do an excellent job in fulfilling your tasks and 
in building the party branch of the company, improve ideological 
education and work style, and successfully conduct military 
training so as to truly satisfactorily accomplish the mission 
assigned by the party and people once an order is given." Zhang 
Zhen lectured the officers and men on the fine traditions of our 
army in light of the company's actual conditions. He said: 
"Our army always obeys the party and, under the party's 
leadership, is capable of withstanding the test of any hardship 
or difficulty and is invincible." He urged all officers and men 
of the company to set an example of safeguarding the party's 
basic line and to resolutely accomplish the mission entrusted by 
the CMC. (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1130 GMT 
31 Jan 94) 
<H3>  Chen Xitong Meets NPC Deputies </H3>
Some National People's Congress (NPC) deputies from Beijing and 
Tianjin concluded their inspection of Beijing on 28 January. 
Chen Xitong, member of the CPC Central Committee Political 
Bureau and secretary of the Beijing municipal party committee, 
and relevant responsible persons of Beijing municipality held a 
meeting with the above- mentioned NPC deputies in the afternoon 
of 28 January and listened to their views and suggestions on 
Beijing's economic and social development. (Beijing Central 
People's Radio Network in Mandarin 1030 GMT 28 Jan 94) 
<H3>  Song Jian Visits Beijing Zoo </H3>
Accompanied by Hou Jie, construction minister; Xie Zhenhua, 
State Environmental Protection Bureau director; and relevant 
leaders of Beijing municipality, State Councillor Song Jian 
visited the Beijing Zoo in the morning of 3 February to wish 
some 3,500 zoo personnel a happy Chinese New Year. (Beijing 
XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1227 GMT 3 Feb 94) 
<H3>  Wu Xueqian at CPPCC Spring Festival Party </H3>
The national committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC] hosted a Spring Festival tea 
party in Beijing on 2 February for widows of deceased members of 
the CPPCC National Committee who were not CPC members and for 
the wives of some celebrities. Cheng Siyuan, vice chairman of 
the National People's Congress [NPC] Standing Committee; Ye 
Xuanping, Wu Xueqian, and Qian Zhengying, vice chairmen of the 
CPPCC national committee; and leading comrades of the NPC 
Standing Committee General Office, State Council General Office, 
CPC Central Committee United Front Work Department, and State 
Council's Government Offices Administration Bureau happily 
gathered with more than 300 ladies to celebrate the coming 
Spring Festival. Qian Zhengying delivered a speech on behalf of 
the CPPCC national committee, calling for concerted efforts to 
further promote China's reform, opening up, and socialist 
modernization in 1994. (Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in 
Chinese 0719 GMT 2 Feb 94) 
<H3>  Zou Jiahua Meets BASF Chairman </H3>
China's Yangzi Petrochemical Company and Germany's BASF Company 
signed agreements in Beijing on three petrochemical joint 
ventures, including a polystyrene project, on 3 February. State 
Council Vice Premier Zou Jiahua met with the BASF chairman and 
his party. Zou Jiahua said: "The Chinese Government welcomes 
investments by big foreign companies in setting up plants in 
China. The large petrochemical joint ventures between Germany's 
BASF and China's Yangzi Petrochemical Company will serve to 
promote economic cooperation between the two countries as well 
as the development of China's petrochemical industry." 
President Sheng Huaren, of the China National Petrochemical 
Corporation [CNPC], presided over the 3 February 
agreement-signing ceremony attended by responsible persons of 
relevant ministries and State Council commissions, the CNPC, 
Jiangsu Province, and Nanjing city. (Beijing XINHUA Domestic 
Service in Chinese 1243 GMT 3 Feb 94) 
<H3>  Wu Bangguo, Huang Ju Visit Servicemen </H3>
On 1 February, Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC Central Committee 
Political Bureau and secretary of the Shanghai municipal party 
committee [SMPC]; Huang Ju, deputy secretary of the SMPC and 
Shanghai mayor; and Chen Zhili, Wang Liping, Chen Liangyu, Chen 
Tiedi, and other leaders of the SMPC, Shanghai Municipal 
People's Congress, Shanghai municipal government, Shanghai 
Municipal Chinese People's Consultative Conference, and Shanghai 
Municipal Discipline Inspection Commission separately called on 
a coastal defense brigade of the Shanghai Garrison, units of the 
Navy and Air Force stationed in Shanghai, an army hospital, an 
Air Force political academy, and armed police detachments in 
Shanghai to convey warm regards to officers and men and to wish 
them a happy Chinese New Year. Shanghai actors and actresses 
accompanied the above-mentioned leaders in their Spring Festival 
calls and staged brilliant performances to entertain the 
officers and men. (Shanghai People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1000 GMT 1 Feb 94) 
<H3>  Wang Hanbin Awards Bridge Players </H3>
A bridge tournament jointly sponsored by the Bridge Association 
of China [BAC] and the Cankun Group was held at the Great Hall 
of the People on 31 January. Wang Hanbin, adviser of the BAC; 
He Guangyuan, director of the CPC Central Committee and state 
organs Bridge Association; and Wu Cankun, president of the 
Cankun Group, gave awards to winners. (Beijing XINHUA Domestic 
Service in Chinese 1443 GMT 31 Jan 94) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

