<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Xichang Satellite Launching Center </TI></H3>
<H4>   Technical Transformation Complete </H4>
<F P=102> HK0802102594 Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0802102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Xichang satellite launch center has smoothly 
completed its large-scale technical transformation. A 
comprehensive appraisal by scientific and technological 
personnel indicates that following this technical 
transformation, the launch facilities can launch many types of 
carrier rockets. China's comprehensive satellite launching 
ability has improved. 
  In 1993, the Xichang satellite launch center carried out a 
large-scale technical transformation, with the support of dozens 
of scientific research and production units throughout the 
country. Technological personnel completed the transformation of 
more than 100 important projects -- including the launch pad 
system, the booster acceleration system, and the testing system 
for rockets and satellites -- thus improving the ability of 
China's space flight industry to join international competition. 

</TEXT>

