<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Council To Cancel Five Tax Items </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0802104594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0611 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0802104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 8 (XINHUA) -- China's State 
Council has decided to cancel five tax items and leave two 
others to the discretion of local governments. 
  The move is aimed at simplifying and standardizing the 
taxation system. 
  The five cancelled taxes are those previously levied on 
trade 
fairs, livestock trading, bonuses and salary adjustments, and 
oil burning. 
  Meanwhile, the power to levy two other taxes -- on animal 
slaughter and banquets -- will be turned over to provincial, 
autonomous regional and municipal governments. 

</TEXT>

