<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stock Exchange Network Takes Shape </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0402053094 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1300 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0402053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 1 Feb (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE) -- After 
several years of steady development, a stock exchange network 
composed of stock exchange centers, securities companies, 
securities business departments, and stock transaction agencies 
has taken shape in the stock market in mainland China, and up to 
150,000 people are working in this profession. 
  It has been learned that the mainland achieved greater 
development in securities administration last year. The State 
Council promulgated the first group of laws and regulations on 
securities management -- "Interim Regulations on the 
Administration of Stock Issue and Transactions" -- to provide 
the stock market with an important legal basis and guarantee. 
  At present, apart from establishing the two stock exchanges 
in Shanghai and Shenzhen, two national stock exchange quotation 
systems have been set up in the mainland. In order to guarantee 
rapid, accurate, and highly effective stock transactions, more 
than 17 regional stock exchange centers -- dealing primarily 
with such transaction items as treasury bonds, local enterprise 
bonds, and investment funds -- and 86 professional companies 
running the business of various securities are being built in 
the mainland. In addition, more than 370 credit investment 
companies have set up securities business departments and there 
are over 2,000 stock transaction agencies spreading all over the 
country. Using such advanced means as computers, this stock 
exchange network helps investors purchase all sorts of 
securities and facilitates stock transactions at any time. 

</TEXT>

