<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Council Sets New Working Hour Limits </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0702030194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0246 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0702030194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 7 (XINHUA) -- Chinese workers will 
get an extra half-day holiday a week starting March 1 this year, 
according to regulations issued by the State Council. 
  The regulations said that workers in Chinese Government 
organs, institutions, enterprises and other organizations will 
work eight hours a day and 44 hours a week from March 1. 
  Units that claim special difficulties in adopting the 
measure 
will be given a two-month grace period to institute the new 
system. 
  Units may shorten working hours if special conditions are 
involved. 
  No one shall extend working hours without authorization. 
When special conditions or urgent tasks call for extension of 
working hours, the relevant state stipulations shall be 
followed, the regulations said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

