<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Calls For Enough Production Means for Farmers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0402132194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1225 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0402132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 4 (XINHUA) -- A senior Chinese 
official today urged the country's trade departments to take 
effective measures to ensure sufficient means of production for 
farmers for the spring ploughing. 
  China's 900 million farmers will face a "severe overall 
shortage" of fertilizers and other means of production this 
spring, said State Councillor Chen Junsheng at a national 
conference on the supply of means of agricultural production. 
  The main suppliers of the country's means of production, the 
domestic trade departments, have bought much less than for last 
year and have less in stock, Chen said. 
  The number of the country's fertilizer plants has shrunk, 
and 
high-quality fertilizer is more urgently needed, he said, noting 
that imported fertilizers have not come as expected. 
  Chen said that domestic trade bodies must resort to all 
possible means to provide enough for the farmers for the spring 
ploughing. 
  He said that good market order should be maintained. Any 
profiteer who infringes upon the interests of farmers will be 
prosecuted to the full extent of the law. 
  Fake and shoddy goods must be barred from the market, so 
that 
high quality means of production can be ensured for farmers, he 
said. 
  He also encouraged the domestic trade departments to reduce 
circulation costs and offer reasonable prices that farmers can 
afford. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

