<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Official Comments on Smooth Transition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0902051294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0427 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902051294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, February 9 (XINHUA) -- The maintenance of 
Macao's stable development and smooth transition conforms to the 
interests of China, Portugal and local people, Guo Dongpo said 
in his spring festival message here today. 
  Guo, director of the XINHUA NEWS AGENCY Macao branch, said 
that in the coming new year, we hope to continue friendly 
cooperation with the Portugal Government in implementing the 
Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration in convergence with the Basic 
Law of Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR), in a bid to 
properly deal with a series of important issues in the 
transitional period. 
  He pointed out, these issues include the three major 
questions, namely localization of public servants and law and 
officialization of Chinese language. 
  In handling some key issues, Guo noted, we hope to, together 
with the Portugal side, seek proper ways to work out solutions 
on the basis of mutual respect and mutual understanding. 
  He added that this would also be done in line with the 
spirit 
of friendly relationship and cooperation between the two 
Governments of China and Portugal, and in the view of Macao's 
long-term interest. 
  He commented that as a result of friendly cooperation 
between 
the two Governments of China and Portugal, all matters 
concerning the transition in Macao have developed smoothly. 
  He hoped that Macao compatriots and people from all walks of 
life continue to actively participate in various matters in the 
transitional period and contribute more to the prosperity and 
bright future of Macao. 

</TEXT>

