<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaison Group Head Stresses Smooth Transition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0902104994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0949 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, February 9 (XINHUA) -- The two sides of the 
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group will make all-out efforts to 
guarantee the smooth transition and transfer of power in Macao 
this year. 
  Ambassador Guo Jiading, leader of the Chinese team, 
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group, said that they would also 
work hard for the long-term stability and development in the 
area. 
  Guo made these remarks in his Spring Festival message 
delivered here today. 
  He said, in 1994 the two sides of the Joint Liaison Group 
would continue discussions on the three major questions in the 
transitional period, namely localization of public servants and 
law as well as officialization of Chinese language. 
  Moreover, talks would also be held between the two sides on 
the retirement pay for public servants, Macao's joining in 
international organizations and many other issues in the 
transitional period. 
  Guo said that 1994 would be a busy year for the Joint 
Liaison 
Group. However, he said he was convinced that all matters would 
be handled properly and timely so long as the two sides firmly 
adhere to the Sino-Portuguese joint declaration and cooperate 
with each other on the bases of mutual respect, mutual 
understanding and sincerity. 

</TEXT>

