<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Tax Payments Up 52 Percent in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0902032094 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0400 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0902032094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A person in charge of the provincial Taxation 
Bureau revealed that the province's taxation showed a strong 
trend of growth last year. Last year tax payments amounted to 
more than 36.3 billion yuan, an increase of 12.56 billion yuan 
over 1992, up by 52 percent. As learned, in the last 14 years 
of reform and opening up, the province's industrial and 
commercial taxes have increased at an annual rate 17.7 percent, 
maintaining simultaneous growth with the province's gross 
domestic product and national income. The proportion of its 
taxation to its GDP has remained at approximately 14 percent, 
far exceeding the country's average. 

</TEXT>

