<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangxi Notes Changes in Grain Production, Consumption </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0902092994 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0811 GMT 
9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0902092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanning, February 9 (CNS) -- The Guangxi Zhuang 
Autonomous Region has seen a change in its grain consumption 
with food grains other than wheat and rice such as corn and 
sweet potatoes being very keenly consumed by people there. 
  Such food as sweet potato, boiled corn, boiled peanuts and 
roasted chestnut are very popular there with the price of baked 
sweet potato increasing to up to 2.5 yuan per jin from several 
fens for each jin while that of rice is mere 1 yuan per jin. 
The profits earned from roasted chestnuts has risen by as much 
as 60 percent, much higher than that earned from rice. 
  An official from the Bureau of Agriculture in the region 
told 
this agency that in order to meet the needs in the market, the 
structure of grain production had changed there with the area 
for rice cultivation reducing while that for sugarcane growing 
increasing and totalling 1.45 million mu. The area under 
cultivation of soya bean, peanut and corn now exceeds 24 million 
mu with the total output increasing by more than 15 percent over 
last year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-26518 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi027_p_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-027 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hainan Makes Progress in Power Station Construction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0902034094 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0902034094 </F>
<F P=104>  Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hainan has made marked achievements in electric 
power development. Last year the province generated 1.9 billion 
kwh, an increase of 33.4 percent over the previous year. The 
gross output value amounted to more than 500 million yuan, an 
increase of 63.1 percent over the previous year. Last year 
electric power departments in the province made great efforts to 
increase electric power generation. [words indistinct] Since 
funding is guaranteed, the Nanshan electric power station can 
smoothly proceed with all its construction projects. Its first 
generating unit is expected to go into operation at the end of 
this February. 
  To guarantee the fulfillment of state key construction 
projects in the province, the Dagongba hydropower station has 
gone into operation earlier than scheduled. Electric power 
departments in the province have opened up all avenues to ensure 
power supply. The Xiubian electric power project, with a total 
investment of 73.95 million yuan, was completed and put into 
operation last October after one year of efforts. [words 
indistinct] 

</TEXT>

