<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Reports Foreign Funds Utilization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0902074694 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0902074694 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The province has accelerated the pace of absorbing 
foreign firms and investment. Last year, the province topped $1 
billion in utilizing foreign funds, an increase of 76 percent 
over the previous year, and a record high in utilizing foreign 
funds since the commencement of reform and opening up. Last 
year, the province continuously improved the investment 
environment and increased the dynamics of absorbing foreign 
firms and investment, thus bringing forth a dramatic atmosphere 
in absorbing foreign firms and investment. Last year, the 
province approved a total of 1,718 projects that utilize foreign 
investment, an increase of 95 percent over the previous year. 
The source of foreign firms and foreign investment and the 
scale and scope of foreign investment were wider than in the 
past. Some internationally noted financial groups, 
transnational corporations, and large corporations arrived in 
the province to investigate and discuss investment projects. 
Thus far, more than 100 foreign corporations have set up 
agencies in the province, and more than 40 foreign countries and 
regions, including Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan, the ROK, and the 
United States, have set up investment projects in the province. 
The province has also witnessed a good trend that large- and 
medium-sized state-owned enterprises have utilized foreign funds 
to conduct renovations. Thus far, more than 500 large- and 
medium-sized enterprises have conducted renovations. By the end 
of 1993, the province approved a total of 3,383 projects 
invested in by foreign corporations, with the contracted value 
of foreign investment reaching $2.38 billion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-26528 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi027_s_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-027 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

