<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-027 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deng Xiaoping Meets Officials During Stay in Shanghai </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Secretary </H4>
<F P=102> OW0902140194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1124 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0902140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Chen Maodi (7115 3029 1717) ] </F>
  [Text] Shanghai, 9 Feb (XINHUA) -- As the Spring Festival, 
a traditional holiday of the Chinese people, draws near, Comrade 
Deng Xiaoping happily got together with responsible party, 
government, and military comrades of Shanghai municipality and 
some veteran comrades this afternoon, exchanging Spring Festival 
greetings and regards. 
  This was the seventh consecutive year Comrade Deng Xiaoping 
joined people in Shanghai to mark the Spring Festival since 1988. 
  The hall of meeting was decorated with flowers and imbued 
with a spring atmosphere. With a smile, Comrade Deng Xiaoping 
walked to the front of the comrades in Shanghai in high spirits 
and with firm strides. Wu Bangguo, member of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Shanghai 
Municipal party committee, and Huang Ju, Shanghai mayor, stepped 
forward to express their sincere blessings to Comrade Xiaoping. 
  Wu Bangguo said: "On behalf of the 13 million people in 
Shanghai, I wish you a happy Spring Festival, health, and long 
life; I wish your whole family happiness." 
  Comrade Deng Xiaoping said: "I wish the leading comrades of 
the central authorities with Comrade Jiang Zemin as the core a 
happy Spring Festival and good health. I wish people throughout 
the country a happy Spring Festival, happy family lives, unity, 
and greater victories in the new year." 
  Comrade Deng Xiaoping said: "I come to Shanghai once a year 
to wish the people in Shanghai a happy Spring Festival." 
  Wu Bangguo said: "This is your encouragement for people in 
Shanghai. It shows your concern and support for the work in 
Shanghai." 
  Comrade Deng Xiaoping said happily: "You people in Shanghai 
have done a really good job in your work." 
  During his stay in Shanghai, Comrade Deng Xiaoping showed 
great concern for Shanghai's material and spiritual 
construction. He fully affirmed the successes achieved by 
people in Shanghai in the past year. He said: "Shanghai has 
accomplished its work very well. Shanghai has special qualities 
and character. Shanghai is fully capable of proceeding faster." 
  On 13 December 1993, Shanghai was engulfed by force 6 chilly 
wind and drizzle. The temperature abruptly dropped to about 
zero degrees Celsius. On the morning of that day, Comrade Deng 
Xiaoping, accompanied by Wu Bangguo, Huang Ju, and others, 
inspected Pudong and ascended the Yangpu Bridge to view the 
teeming construction in Pudong. Having inspected the Pudong 
section of the inner ring and the two overpasses over Luoshan 
Road and Longyang Road, which were completed last year, Comrade 
Xiaoping said with a smile: "Watching these roads with joy 
today is better than reading books for 100 years." He told 
Comrades Wu Bangguo and Huang Ju: "These words are from the 
bottom of my heart." 
  Standing on the magnificent Yangpu Bridge, Comrade Xiaoping 
held the hands of Zhu Zhihao, chief commander of the 
construction of the bridge, and praised him: "This is a victory 
of the Shanghai working class. I salute the Shanghai working 
class!" 
  On the eve of the New Year, in the company of Wu Bangguo, 
Huang Ju, and others, Comrade Deng Xiaoping ascended to the top 
floor of the Jinjiang Tower, looking down the brightly 
illuminated Shanghai streets. He said: "Shanghai has changed." 
Seeing Comrade Deng Xiaoping unexpectedly, Chinese and foreign 
tourists marking the holiday at the hotel could not but give him 
a long applause and express their respect and best wishes to 
him. With a smile, Comrade Xiaoping waved to them in 
acknowledgement. This evening, he also went to the congested 
Nanjing Road and the bund to enjoy the jubilation of the holiday 
with people in Shanghai. 
  Comrade Deng Xiaoping was very pleased to hear that the 
Dayawan Nuclear Power Plant No. 1 generator unit had been 
successfully put into operation. This morning, he asked Comrade 
Li Peng to convey his congratulations and gratitude to the 
builders, scientists, and technicians of Dayawan Nuclear Power 
Plant. 

</TEXT>

