<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spring Festival Wishes Passed to Peng Zhen, Wan Li </TI></H3>
<H4>   Discuss `Main Work' </H4>
<F P=102> OW0902130394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1247 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 9 (XINHUA) -- Jiang Zemin and 
other top leaders, Monday [7 February] called on Peng Zhen and 
Wan Li, both former chairmen of China's National People's 
Congress Standing Committee, on separate occasions. 
  On behalf of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central 
Committee and the State Council, General Secretary Jiang Zemin, 
Liu Huaqing and Hu Jintao, all Standing Committee members of the 
Political Bureau of the party Central Committee, extended spring 
festival greetings to the two veteran leaders. 
  At the residences of Peng and Wan, Jiang presented them with 
fresh flowers and asked about their living and health. He 
briefed the two retired leaders on the main work done by the 
party Central Committee and the State Council last year, and the 
basic principles governing this year's work. 
  Jiang expressed the hope that retired veteran leaders will 
continue making proposals regarding the work of the party 
central committee, and make greater contributions to the 
country's economic construction and reforms and opening. 
  Peng and Wan asked the visitors to convey their thanks and 
spring festival greetings to the leaders of the party Central 
Committee and the State Council. 
  Peng and Wan expressed their gratification over the 
achievements China scored in reforms and opening and in 
construction over the past year. They said they hoped that the 
country will win even greater victories in the new year in 
economic construction, reforms and opening up and in maintaining 
social stability. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

