<H3> <TI>   Spring Festival Wishes Passed to Peng Zhen, Wan Li </TI></H3>
<H4>   Voice `Support' to Li </H4>
<F P=102> OW0902130494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1249 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 9 (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng 
today called on Peng Zhen and Wan Li, both former chairmen of 
the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, 
extending spring festival greetings to them. 
  Li, who has just returned to Beijing from an inspection 
tour, 
presented flower baskets to the two retired leaders, and wished 
them good health and happy new year. 
  Li, also a Standing Committee member of the Communist 
Party's 
Politburo, briefed Peng and Wan on the current domestic 
situation and a series of policies and measures taken by the 
party Central Committee and the State Council to develop the 
economy and push ahead with reform and opening. He also 
solicited their opinions and proposals on different aspects of 
work. 
  Peng and Wan voiced satisfaction with the work of the party 
Central Committee and the State Council as well as happiness 
with the economic development, reform and opening. Also, they 
expressed full support to the principle governing work in 1994 
formulated by the party Central Committee, that is, to seize the 
current opportunity for development, deepen reforms, open China 
wider to the outside world, promote economic growth and maintain 
stability. 
  They also expressed the hope that the party Central 
Committee 
and the State Council will continue to lead the Chinese people 
of various nationalities in working hard to score still greater 
achievements in the new year. 

</TEXT>

