<H3> <TI>   Leaders Exchange Spring Festival Greetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Li Peng Greets Guangdong </H4>
<F P=102> HK0902143594 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0902143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a report by a staff reporter of the 
Guangdong television station, from 28 January to 8 February, 
State Council Prime Minister Li Peng made an inspection tour of 
Guangdong. Those who accompanied Premier Li Peng on his 
inspection tour included Ding Guangen, member of the CPC 
Committee Political Bureau; Xie Fei, member of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau and secretary of the Guangdong 
provincial party committee; Guangdong Governor Zhu Senlin; and 
responsible comrades of the relevant departments under the State 
Council. 
  In Guangdong, Li Peng successively inspected projects for 
basic facilities, as well as some hi-tech and new projects in 
Foshan, Zhongshan, Zhuhai, Shenzhen, Huizhou, and other places. 
He also had discussions with local party and government leading 
comrades. Premier Li Peng and other leading comrades also 
visited holiday markets, and conveyed their spring festival 
greetings to Guangdong people. Comrade Li Peng said: 
  [Begin recording] Guangdong is a forward position of reform 
and opening up. It has done very well in various aspects. I 
wish Guangdong people a still greater success in the new year 
under the guidance of the spirit of the 14th CPC National 
Congress and the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central 
Committee. I wish them good health, and hope that everything 
will turn out as they wish. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

