<H3> <TI>   Leaders Exchange Spring Festival Greetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao Greet Bo Yibo, Song Ping </H4>
<F P=102> OW0902134794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1339 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 9 (XINHUA) -- Senior leaders Li 
Ruihuan and Hu Jintao, on behalf of the Chinese Communist Party 
(CPC) Central Committee and the State Council, on Monday [7 
February] paid a New Year call and extended Spring Festival 
greetings to retired veteran leaders Song Ping, Bo Yibo and Song 
Renqiong. 
  Li and Hu, both members of the Standing Committee of the 
Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central 
Committee, asked the three veterans about their welfare and 
health, and briefed them on the current domestic situation and 
the basic policies regarding this year's work. 
  Li and Hu expressed the hope that retired veteran leaders 
would make more proposals on the work of the party central 
committee and the State Council and help the party Central 
Committee to make a good job of every endeavor. 
  Song Ping, Bo Yibo and Song Renqiong asked Li and Hu to 
convey their thanks and Spring Festival greetings to the leaders 
of the party Central Committee and the State Council. 
  They said that since the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC 
Central 
Committee was held the situation in the country has been getting 
better and better with each passing day, and the country's 
economy is developing at a fast speed, increasing the nation's 
strength and improving the people's living standards. 
  They stressed the need to further emancipate the mind, seek 
truth from facts, and continue to advance along the road of 
socialism with Chinese characteristics, so as to strive to 
realize the second-step strategic target ahead of schedule and 
achieve greater victories. 

</TEXT>

