  [Text] Beijing, February 9 (XINHUA) -- Vice-Premier Li 
Lanqing visited Tianqiao Department Store and Hongqiao 
Agricultural Produce Free Market in Beijing today, the eve of 
the Spring Festival. 
  At Tianqiao Department Store, Li exchanged festival 
greetings 
with customers and sales staff. He was pleased with the store's 
extensive array of beautifully-lit counters with commodities. 
  Li, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist 
Party's Central Committee, was equally happy to see the 
plentiful supplies of goods served at the agricultural produce 
market. He expressed festival greetings to the personnel of the 
Administration of Industry and Commerce. 
  The Administration of Industry and Commerce is one of the 
major departments to implement laws and regulations and it plays 
an important role in ensuring the smooth development of the 
reforms, he said. 
  Li urged the personnel of the Administration of Industry and 
Commerce to make a bigger contribution to the development of the 
national economy. 

