<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Inspects Zhuhai Special Economic Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0902043094 Hong Kong WEN WEI PO in Chinese 9 Feb 94 p A2 </F>
<F P=103> HK0902043094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong WEN WEI PO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dispatch: "Li Peng Inspects Zhuhai and Huizhou"] </F>
  [Text] Zhuhai, 8 Feb (WEN WEI PO) -- During an inspection 
tour of Zhuhai a few days ago, Li Peng, member of the Standing 
Committee of the CPC Central Committee's Political Bureau and 
State Council premier, said that Zhuhai's growth has been rapid. 
Instead of asking the state for money to carry out capital 
construction, Zhuhai has relied on its own efforts to develop a 
lot of basic facilities. This move is correct and it has offered 
a good example to the whole country. 
  Premier Li Peng made an inspection tour of Zhuhai from 29 
January to 4 February. During these seven days, Premier Li Peng 
went to construction sites, enterprises, and the grass-roots 
levels to conduct investigation and study; inspected the 
construction of the Qiao Bridge, the Zhuhai Bridge, the first of 
its kind in southern Guangdong, which was open to traffic by the 
end of last year, the Juren Holdings Company, and Zhuhai's urban 
construction and management; and listened to accounts given by 
the city party secretary and mayor Liang Guangda and other 
leaders. Premier Li Peng was pleased at the results of his 
on-the-spot inspection and the accounts given to him. He fully 
affirmed the work of the city leading body and spoke highly of 
and expressed satisfaction at Zhuhai's economic construction, 
urban building and management, environmental protection, 
hygiene, land management, afforestation, population control, 
social security, and overall administration. Zhuhai is indeed a 
beautiful city. The climate is pleasant and warm as in spring. 
I came here last year. During the current trip, I have 
witnessed the tremendous changes. With its rapid economic 
development and beautiful urban planning, Zhuhai is indeed a 
match for the cities of the developed nations. 
  Through the in-depth inspection of Zhuhai, Premier Li Peng 
said that Zhuhai's reform, opening up, and economic construction 
are successful. He spoke highly of the unremitting efforts made 
by Zhuhai to overcome difficulties and implement the central 
policy of reform and opening up, and the spirit of continuously 
forging ahead and advancing amid storms. He specially presented 
Zhuhai with the poem "Ode to the Bamboo" by Qing poet Zheng 
Qiao: "Taking root in the steep rocks of the mountain, it 
remains firm and strong despite being buffeted by winds from all 
sides." Premier Li Peng encouraged Zhuhai party and government 
leaders and party members to earnestly study Volume 3 of the 
Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping, make bold 
explorations and practice, and constantly attain new 
achievements in establishing a socialist market economy and 
building socialism with Chinese characteristics. 
  Premier Li Peng left Zhuhai for an inspection of Shenzhen on 
the morning of 4 February. 

</TEXT>

