<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports on Satellite Launch 8 Feb </TI></H3>
<H4>   Government Hails Launch </H4>
<F P=102> OW0902085094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0801 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0902085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 9 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese State 
Council and the Central Military Commission extended 
congratulations to staff and workers engaged in launching 
satellites. 
  China successfully launched a scientific satellite and a 
simulated satellite into space from the Xichang launch site in 
southwest China yesterday afternoon. 
  In a message of congratulations today, the State Council and 
the commission lauded the launching, which it called "another 
important achievement in China's high-tech space research field." 
  The message went on, "It will have a notable impact on 
efforts to accomplish China's strategic objective of developing 
a new generation of multi-purpose satellites, and expanding 
exchanges and co-operation with overseas in the space field." 

</TEXT>

