<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Attends `Factories in Difficulty' Forum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0802152694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1449 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0802152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chengdu, February 8 (XINHUA) -- Vice-Premier Zhu 
Rongji has toured southwest China's Sichuan Province, where he 
saw local party and government leaders and retired cadres, 
visited research institutions and factories and attended a 
seminar of factories in difficulty. 
  Zhu, member of the Standing Committee of the Political 
Bureau 
of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, praised 
Sichuan for its achievements in various sectors and its efforts 
to properly handle the relations between the reforms, 
development and stability. 
  On January 6, Zhu paid a visit to the Chongqing No.1 Textile 
Mill, where he called a meeting of nine enterprises in 
difficulty to discuss with them how to end their plight. 
  Zhu Rongji said that the establishment of a modern 
enterprise 
system required that the government kept its hands off 
enterprises, allowing them to enjoy decision-making powers and 
managers to bear full responsibility for their decisions. 
  He said that for enterprises which continually suffer losses 
and cannot pay their debts, an experimental bankruptcy policy 
can be applied so as to reorganize them. 
  He also stressed the importance of reforming the social 
security system so that the enterprises can smoothly transform 
their system and maintain stability. 
  He urged managers and directors to overcome their 
difficulties mainly on their own by developing new products and 
studying the market, improving management and transforming the 
operational system. 
  He called on them to show more concern for the living of 
their employees. 

</TEXT>

